Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.90,0:00:08.18,Default,G,0,0,0,,Hey, talk about a reversal of fortunes, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.70,0:00:20.12,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.00,0:00:27.49,Title,Ep Title,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,255)}Night of Miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.49,0:01:55.54,Default,G,0,0,0,,She can't see you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.54,0:01:56.76,Default,G,0,0,0,,What does that even mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.76,0:01:59.34,Default,P,0,0,0,,Well, how should I explain?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.34,0:02:03.50,Default,P,0,0,0,,Oh, an old fortune teller with the traveling \Nentertainers used to say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.50,0:02:07.37,Default,P,0,0,0,,Um, those with a rigid\Nworld view can't see fae.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.37,0:02:08.27,Default,P,0,0,0,,I think that was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:09.34,Default,G,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.34,0:02:10.77,Default,G,0,0,0,,A rigid world view, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.93,0:02:13.69,Default,P,0,0,0,,Guts!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.98,0:02:15.94,Default,G,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.41,0:02:17.71,Default,G,0,0,0,,Here they come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:19.82,Default,F,0,0,0,,My allies?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.95,0:02:35.89,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.32,0:02:37.82,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.36,0:02:48.61,Default,G,0,0,0,,Take a good look, with wide-open eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.24,0:02:52.06,Default,G,0,0,0,,They're miracles, sent to this world by God,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.06,0:02:55.74,Default,G,0,0,0,,that you can't see just by worshiping an idol.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.53,0:03:01.62,Default,G,0,0,0,,I see it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.60,0:03:03.61,Default,F,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.61,0:03:06.39,Default,G,0,0,0,,That's where I was headed to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.69,0:03:10.59,Default,G,0,0,0,,Though there's been lots of interference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.59,0:03:11.78,Default,F,0,0,0,,What's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.05,0:03:14.27,Default,G,0,0,0,,Didn't you want to know what I was after?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.27,0:03:15.00,Default,F,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:16.11,Default,G,0,0,0,,It's just as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.11,0:03:17.50,Default,G,0,0,0,,I'll tell you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:22.55,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.29,0:03:27.43,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,The estate of Count Lansdown, \Nwho governed Midland's western outskirts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.43,0:03:33.00,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,Loving hunting and hounds, he built this \Nmanse at which to while away his idleness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.00,0:03:36.53,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,The fire five years ago, which killed \Nthe count and his retainers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.53,0:03:38.61,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,should have reduced it to mere ruins...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.02,0:03:41.37,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.37,0:03:46.91,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,reports said that travelers and pilgrims \Noften go missing in these parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.77,0:04:11.85,Default,G,0,0,0,,What a sad end for the former hounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.25,0:04:14.33,Default,G,0,0,0,,They're excited by the smell of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.16,0:04:24.25,Default,F,0,0,0,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.25,0:04:25.69,Default,F,0,0,0,,How can such things...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.93,0:04:28.82,Default,G,0,0,0,,...even exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.82,0:04:30.49,Default,G,0,0,0,,That's why I called them miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.20,0:04:41.85,Default,G,0,0,0,,How can you be terrified of \Nsuch a great opportunity?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.85,0:04:44.11,Default,G,0,0,0,,As a believer, don't you have some phrase?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:46.96,Default,G,0,0,0,,You could say, "Dear God..."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.75,0:04:54.27,Default,G,0,0,0,,I've had my fill of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.33,0:04:57.27,Default,G,0,0,0,,Enough to make me puke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.70,0:04:59.93,Default,G,0,0,0,,Come with me, or you'll be devoured!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.97,0:05:14.29,Default,F,0,0,0,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.13,0:05:17.66,Default,P,0,0,0,,Man, that was tough...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.66,0:05:19.52,Default,G,0,0,0,,What, you even brought the horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.52,0:05:20.77,Default,P,0,0,0,,Hey, Guts!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.77,0:05:22.56,Default,P,0,0,0,,You seem not to have gotten \Nit through your skull—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:24.28,Default,G,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.28,0:05:27.43,Default,G,0,0,0,,I'll never forget that you brought \Nme all the way here, horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.43,0:05:28.55,Default,P,0,0,0,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.33,0:05:36.98,Default,P,0,0,0,,Man, those are a lot of heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.43,0:05:39.58,Default,P,0,0,0,,Humans, I tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.58,0:05:42.48,Default,P,0,0,0,,Oh, Divine Lord, show mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.12,0:05:46.01,Default,G,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.49,0:05:47.99,Default,P,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing really.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.02,0:05:59.10,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,What in the world is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.47,0:06:05.16,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,What misshapen, abhorrent creatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.16,0:06:08.01,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,Does this have to do with what \NRevelations foretold, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.13,0:06:12.51,Default,F,0,0,0,,Serpico?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.50,0:06:15.52,Default,G,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.33,0:06:26.53,Default,G,0,0,0,,That idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.11,0:06:33.22,Default,F,0,0,0,,A man?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.06,0:06:36.21,Default,F,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.21,0:06:38.38,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,That's my line.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.38,0:06:41.80,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I am this place's keeper of the hounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.62,0:06:44.83,Default,F,0,0,0,,Very well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.83,0:06:47.31,Default,F,0,0,0,,First, untie me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.31,0:06:49.68,Default,F,0,0,0,,I'll see that you are rewarded \Nhandsomely for your aid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:50.85,Default,F,0,0,0,,I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.04,0:06:54.70,Default,F,0,0,0,,I am in this state for reasons I cannot say,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.70,0:06:57.13,Default,F,0,0,0,,but I am a legitimate Holy See knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.13,0:06:58.89,Default,F,0,0,0,,I will ensure you are well-received.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.89,0:07:00.62,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Meat...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:01.74,Default,F,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.74,0:07:06.19,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,It's easier to eat the way it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.38,0:07:21.75,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,H-H-Hounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.90,0:07:25.73,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Don't be cruel to the hounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.73,0:07:28.91,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,They're my... my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.91,0:07:30.37,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Don't hurt them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.37,0:07:32.50,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,You... You'll pay for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.50,0:07:35.15,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Even the master of the house...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.15,0:07:40.51,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,is fed to the dogs if he... if he is cruel to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.51,0:07:42.52,Default,G,0,0,0,,You killed the master of the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.02,0:07:45.73,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,No, I ate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.53,0:07:51.04,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I... I haven't smelled anything \Nthis good in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.04,0:07:54.61,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,A high-quality noblewoman...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.33,0:08:02.08,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I kn-know... y-your smell...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.08,0:08:04.27,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,That was the best prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.27,0:08:08.58,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,You are a survivor from that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.65,0:08:19.30,Default,G,0,0,0,,I won't be lame and try to \Ngo easy with my injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.90,0:08:22.39,Default,G,0,0,0,,I couldn't care less if my arm gets ripped off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:26.19,Default,G,0,0,0,,For the first time in a long while, I remember
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.19,0:08:28.49,Default,G,0,0,0,,how it felt at the start of all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.05,0:08:32.50,Default,G,0,0,0,,Thanks, it feels like crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.78,0:08:35.04,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Me... Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.04,0:08:36.60,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.29,0:08:39.43,Default,G,0,0,0,,See, he's finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.84,0:08:42.85,Default,G,0,0,0,,My target, the one you\Nwanted to know about...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.00,0:08:46.20,Default,G,0,0,0,,The Apostle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.65,0:08:49.86,Default,F,0,0,0,,Apostle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.86,0:08:50.89,Default,G,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.89,0:08:54.01,Default,G,0,0,0,,Eradicating every last one of these Apostles...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:55.52,Default,G,0,0,0,,That is my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.24,0:09:08.79,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Th-The moment that brand marked you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.79,0:09:13.22,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Your... Your fate was set in stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.22,0:09:17.08,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,You're just p-prey... meat... hunted...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.08,0:09:19.77,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,s-struggling... crawling!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.84,0:09:32.35,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Like I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.35,0:09:35.24,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Don't be cruel to the hounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.24,0:09:35.97,Default,P,0,0,0,,Guts, above you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.97,0:09:37.80,Default,G,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.10,0:09:56.87,Default,P,0,0,0,,What's wrong with you, Guts?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.87,0:09:58.22,Default,P,0,0,0,,Do it like usual!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.22,0:10:01.59,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Meat... Meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.99,0:10:07.96,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Meat... Meat...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:15.28,Default,G,0,0,0,,I'm tough and taste like shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.71,0:10:17.65,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.65,0:10:19.24,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,After eating you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.24,0:10:24.20,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I'll c-cleanse my palate...\Nwith the woman-meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.22,0:10:27.83,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Th-That woman... is like the lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.83,0:10:29.96,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,A noblewoman...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.96,0:10:32.30,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,So soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.86,0:10:37.23,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,M-Melting in your mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:39.03,Default,P,0,0,0,,The lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.26,0:10:48.52,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Th-The flavors are coming out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.52,0:10:52.28,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Humans who oppose us...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.28,0:10:55.80,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,are just food.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.89,0:11:00.76,Default,G,0,0,0,,I gotta say, when it comes to eating, \Nyou have no table manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.76,0:11:02.35,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.35,0:11:07.02,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,M-Meat has high... and low grades...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.02,0:11:14.40,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,People nice to me have... s-soft, sweet meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.40,0:11:21.43,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,M-Meat from those... who call me ugly... \Na-and inferior is low-grade!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:24.66,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Smelly meat... tough meat...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.66,0:11:26.65,Default,G,0,0,0,,Then I doubt I'd taste good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.65,0:11:27.84,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,No hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.84,0:11:30.71,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I'll know soon enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.71,0:11:32.63,Default,P,0,0,0,,Hey, Guts!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.63,0:11:34.84,Default,P,0,0,0,,Th-This is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.84,0:11:38.13,Default,P,0,0,0,,This is a real, preserved human being!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:42.97,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Don't touch her!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.32,0:11:57.64,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.64,0:12:00.82,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Don't touch the lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.41,0:12:12.18,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,My lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:49.08,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Sh-She believed in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.48,0:12:53.46,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,They looked down... on me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.46,0:12:57.18,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,as ugly and inferior.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.18,0:13:04.97,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,The lady was the only one... \Nwho believed me, and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.35,0:13:17.86,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,M-My lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.86,0:13:21.10,Default,G,0,0,0,,So you dressed up the half-eaten \Nremains as a tribute to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.60,0:13:25.52,Default,G,0,0,0,,Talk about twisted to the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.95,0:13:26.82,Default,P,0,0,0,,Guts...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.12,0:13:29.66,Default,G,0,0,0,,I will eradicate every last Apostle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.30,0:13:32.52,Default,G,0,0,0,,I'll give you a clean death, so talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.42,0:13:36.02,Default,G,0,0,0,,How can I find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.02,0:13:37.65,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,Them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.53,0:13:42.21,Default,G,0,0,0,,The God Hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.57,0:13:44.41,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I... I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.41,0:13:47.72,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I know nothing about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.60,0:13:52.83,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,They are special...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.83,0:13:56.88,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,R-Really, I d-don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.88,0:14:00.73,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I said I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.62,0:14:06.07,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.07,0:14:08.10,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,I can't think of anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.51,0:14:10.91,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,Not even a single prayer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.94,0:14:16.70,Default,Keeper,0,0,0,,I... I don't... know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.74,0:14:18.95,Default,G,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.43,0:14:34.89,Default,F,0,0,0,,I'll ride this horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.65,0:14:37.73,Default,Horse,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.52,0:14:48.09,Default,Horse,0,0,0,,I'll ride woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:54.74,Default,Horse,0,0,0,,Female. Meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.74,0:14:57.34,Default,Horse,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.91,0:15:01.71,Default,F,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:29.30,Default,G,0,0,0,,Don't run around if you want to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.16,0:15:31.37,Default,F,0,0,0,,Ye...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.73,0:15:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.93,0:15:38.32,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,I'm just running around,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.90,0:15:41.19,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,trembling with fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:46.49,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,I couldn't even beseech God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.35,0:15:49.51,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,And I call myself His servant...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.86,0:15:55.99,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,I've said His name a million times.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.74,0:15:58.21,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,But I am only
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.52,0:16:00.86,Default - italics,,0,0,0,,weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.25,0:16:02.75,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,wretched,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.32,0:16:04.77,Default - italics,,0,0,0,,and powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:08.71,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,Just powerless?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.71,0:16:11.65,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,Just powerless, so you are innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:14.47,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,Don't deceive yourself with pretty words.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.88,0:16:17.06,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,Within you lies
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.06,0:16:20.12,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,a dark desire you cannot tell anyone else about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.61,0:16:22.58,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,You felt it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.58,0:16:25.79,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,You felt a dismal lust as you struck that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.65,0:16:35.69,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,That wasn't the only time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.69,0:16:38.80,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,Even when whipping yourself \Nin the name of atonement,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.80,0:16:43.25,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,you found pleasure within that agony...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.84,0:16:46.85,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,There is no God in any of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.85,0:16:50.40,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,This festering desire is the only truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.40,0:16:53.53,Apostle - Default,Evil,0,0,0,,God is too far removed from the likes of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:02.23,Default,P,0,0,0,,Guts...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.73,0:17:06.63,Default,G,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.15,0:17:20.70,Default,G,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.15,0:17:27.08,Default,P,0,0,0,,Guts, she's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.05,0:17:34.60,Default,G,0,0,0,,You let yourself get possessed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.62,0:17:43.86,Default,F,0,0,0,,Pull this sword up very slowly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.29,0:17:50.11,Default,F,0,0,0,,Feel it with me... This pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:17:55.43,Default,F,0,0,0,,Slowly tear me apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.12,0:18:17.61,Default,F,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.61,0:18:19.01,Default,G,0,0,0,,Hey, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.05,0:18:27.24,Default,F,0,0,0,,Kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.54,0:18:30.75,Default,F,0,0,0,,Kill that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.75,0:18:33.52,Default,F,0,0,0,,Right now, right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:36.91,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Please calm down, Lady Farnese.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.91,0:18:38.87,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.87,0:18:41.65,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,but our original mission was \Nto capture him, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.65,0:18:43.89,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,You should avoid being swayed by—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:43.89,Default,F,0,0,0,,I don't care!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:44.85,Default,F,0,0,0,,Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.85,0:18:47.33,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,To be blunt, I can't. Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.33,0:18:50.68,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,You saw it yourself, Commander.\NHe has superhuman strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.68,0:18:51.77,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,I'd just die a meaningless death—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.54,0:18:53.32,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.07,0:18:55.77,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Oh, Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.85,0:19:00.18,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,There you go, making our commander cry again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.18,0:19:01.45,Default,G,0,0,0,,Not my problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.20,0:19:05.38,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Well, we shall take our leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.38,0:19:08.12,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,That is, if you are willing to let us go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.53,0:19:10.69,Default,G,0,0,0,,I think I owe you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.25,0:19:12.56,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:15.08,Default,G,0,0,0,,Heh, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.00,0:19:22.23,Default,G,0,0,0,,Not a bad move, drawing your sword like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.37,0:19:24.43,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,I'll say the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:26.16,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,You are formidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.45,0:19:28.59,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,So, till we meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.17,0:19:29.94,Default,G,0,0,0,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.94,0:19:31.47,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,For now, it is farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.47,0:19:32.73,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Same to you, pipsqueak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.92,0:19:36.52,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,What a joker.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.98,0:19:41.95,Default,P,0,0,0,,But you know, I feel kind of \Nsorry for that Farnese girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.95,0:19:44.43,Default,P,0,0,0,,She's like, all tightly wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.43,0:19:46.94,Default,G,0,0,0,,I'm the one who's wound up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.85,0:19:49.95,Default,G,0,0,0,,First a ghost, and now a cleric.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.95,0:19:51.35,Default,G,0,0,0,,Talk about annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.05,0:19:56.21,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Commander, wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.16,0:19:58.46,Default - italics,FP,0,0,0,,I have to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.87,0:20:00.20,Default - italics,FP,0,0,0,,I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.74,0:20:02.19,Default - italics,FP,0,0,0,,I have to!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.34,0:20:08.47,Default - italics,FP,0,0,0,,If I don't silence him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.41,0:20:12.97,Default - italics,FP,0,0,0,,If he continues to live, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.00,0:20:22.31,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,They saw the same visions in their dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.28,0:20:26.70,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,There were villages decimated by disease,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.26,0:20:31.18,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,and nations overrun by armies \Nthat commanded giant beasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.98,0:20:36.15,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,There were cities crushed by earthquakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.15,0:20:38.56,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,and towns swallowed by floods.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.16,0:20:43.51,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,The Sun hidden by a thick, black smoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.51,0:20:46.44,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,and wandering throngs of starving people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.98,0:20:52.44,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,There were bodies of entire families, \Nand bodies of their neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.22,0:20:55.14,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,Each saw a myriad of varieties,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.14,0:20:59.32,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,but all pointed toward a singular intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.25,0:21:02.00,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,Each enduring their own night,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.00,0:21:04.98,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,the people were trapped in true darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.98,0:21:07.42,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,that enveloped their shared world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.54,0:21:10.75,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,And amidst the ensuing chaos,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.75,0:21:12.79,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,they observed with keen interest
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.55,0:21:18.81,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,a shining hawk, piercing the infinite gloom,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.81,0:21:21.66,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,and descending upon the bloodstained land.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.72,0:21:24.51,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,They knew immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.01,0:21:28.37,Default - italics,Narr,0,0,0,,that this was their greatest desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.44,0:21:39.16,Default,King,0,0,0,,Charlotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.16,0:21:40.19,Default,King,0,0,0,,Charlo...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.39,0:21:41.32,Default,Servant,0,0,0,,Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:42.72,Default,Phys,0,0,0,,Please bring his relatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.72,0:21:43.78,Default,Phys,0,0,0,,Quickly, I beg you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.27,0:21:48.17,Default,Nobles,0,0,0,,At last...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.17,0:21:50.41,Default,Nobles,0,0,0,,At long last, we'll have a new queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.41,0:21:52.13,Default,Nobles,0,0,0,,Her Majesty, Queen Charlotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.13,0:21:54.46,Default,Nobles,0,0,0,,Given her nature, she will appoint a regent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.46,0:21:56.54,Default,Nobles,0,0,0,,We should plan accordingly...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.54,0:21:59.47,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,Do those dolts even\Nunderstand what's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.47,0:22:01.56,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,It was only thanks to His Majesty
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.56,0:22:04.79,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,that we survived the war with Chuder.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.79,0:22:05.75,Default,Fos,0,0,0,,The hawk...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.68,0:22:09.39,Default,Fos,0,0,0,,The hawk will return.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.89,0:22:12.93,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,The hawk...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.51,0:22:15.56,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,A strange hawk of light that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.56,0:22:19.68,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,the people of Windham... nay, \Nall of Midland saw in dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.68,0:22:22.15,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,Though His Majesty was noble and just,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.15,0:22:25.83,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,he became inscrutable in many of his \Nactions after the Battle of Doldrey.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.83,0:22:27.59,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,The Band of the Hawk's alleged treason...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.59,0:22:30.39,Default - italics,Laban,0,0,0,,Did that really happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.42,0:22:34.38,Default,Maid,0,0,0,,Your Highness, please open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.72,0:22:36.33,Default,Laban,0,0,0,,What is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.33,0:22:38.33,Default,Maid,0,0,0,,General Laban, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.33,0:22:41.98,Default,Maid,0,0,0,,Her Highness hasn't left her \Nchambers in five whole days.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.98,0:22:45.94,Default,Maid,0,0,0,,Only her favorite lady-in-waiting \Nis allowed to enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.94,0:22:48.34,Default,Maid,0,0,0,,She's trying to persuade Her \NHighness right now, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.34,0:22:50.34,Default,Anna,0,0,0,,Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.34,0:22:52.18,Default,Anna,0,0,0,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.79,0:23:07.82,Default,Laban,0,0,0,,Allow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.47,0:23:09.36,Default,Laban,0,0,0,,Your Highness,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:11.09,Default,Laban,0,0,0,,His Majesty is in critical condition!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.59,0:23:12.37,Default,Anna,0,0,0,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.67,0:23:14.50,Default,King,0,0,0,,Griffith...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.05,0:23:21.13,Default,King,0,0,0,,Where are... you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.70,0:23:29.76,Default,Ch,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.07,0:23:35.89,Default,Citizens,0,0,0,,His Majesty has passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.89,0:23:37.32,Default,Citizens,0,0,0,,Now, of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.32,0:23:38.89,Default,Citizens,0,0,0,,What will happen now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.33,0:23:42.87,Default - italics,Ch,0,0,0,,Please save me, Lord Griffith!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:47.09,Default,Kid,0,0,0,,The mountain's moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.93,0:24:01.37,Title2,,0,0,0,,Next Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.37,0:24:05.38,EndInsert,Sign 2405,0,0,0,,Is Casca alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.13,0:24:09.47,EndInsert,Sign 2408,0,0,0,,I'll never lose her again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.43,0:24:13.43,EndInsert,Sign 2412,0,0,0,,Come back again, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.43,0:24:17.43,EndInsert,Sign 2416,0,0,0,,There is something I must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.43,0:24:21.44,EndInsert,Sign 2420,0,0,0,,You claim it's divine punishment?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.85,0:24:27.57,Title2,Sign 2425,0,0,0,,Next Episode \NEpiphany
